 <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Restrictions:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
1.- <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>No extremely big mechas</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: can be from matchbox size up to 30 ft. Can be a suit, although is not recomended as dismembering may occur to your character <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
2.- No background, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>just a good mecha design</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (front, side and back if possible).<br>
3.- If this post has a good acceptance, there will be only <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3 slots available</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for a 2 on 2 fight, the winners of each will fight each other. Constestants will be chosen by me and contacted through e-mail (remember to post your e-mail) The others will be waiting for a slot to be open (if someone doesn't appear)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Fight system</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:<br>
1.- <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Only a page per post</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: The page must show a succesful attack and the opening for the next, so the challenger can draw how to repel or dodge the attack, succesful counter-attack and opening for the next attack, and so on. If after many attempts you cannot figure out how to squish all the action in a page, make two. <br>
2.- <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The fights will last ten rounds</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: being a round a page from each contestant. No dismembering attacks before 7th round.<br>
3.- <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The winner will be chosen by the public</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and if there isn't any, the contestants will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>assign points</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (code of honor, if you think the other had better ideas than you, just say so) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>by round</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, like boxing (10 winner of round, 9 looser of round, 8 if it's a mayor round defeat)<br>
4.- (Idea stolen from Mr. Funk, ruler of the fightclub) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>each contestant <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">MUST</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> post within a week of his/her turn</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, unless he has the proper request for delay and approval from the other contestant. After forfeitting for 2 rounds, in a row or not justified, will occur an automate destruction of the mecha and another in line will be deployed. Points will be reset and the fight will continue through the 10th round. This is to ensure continuity.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">IMPORTANT NOTICE</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Assign points with this in mind if possible:<br>
 MAINLY: good flow of action, good panneling: How well you understand what's going on in the page<br>
 Secondary: How good the attack idea is (if he doesn't repeat itself, etc.)<br>
 Terciary: the quality of the artwork, if the characters are recognizable, how well can represent the other person's character.<br>
<br>
